"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-technology-paris-olympics-crowd-scans-fuel-ai-surveillance-fears\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"SUMMARY This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 69, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.174542916603909e-20, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"errors\", \"from\": 59, \"to\": 65}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For context, always refer to the full article.\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"context\", \"from\": 74, \"to\": 81}, {\"ngram\": \"the full article\", \"from\": 99, \"to\": 115}]}, {\"sentence\": \"OLYMPICS RINGS.\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 133, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"OLYMPICS RINGS\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic rings are displayed on the first floor of the Eiffel Tower ahead of the Paris 2024 Olympic games in Paris, France, June 9, 2024 Benoit Tessier/Reuters LONDON, United Kingdom - French plans to use artificial intelligence (AI) to scan the thousands of athletes, coaches and spectators descending on Paris for the Olympics is a form of creeping surveillance, rights groups said.\", \"from\": 134, \"to\": 523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 246, \"end\": 251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.450025504870683e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 253, \"end\": 259, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9977704980706663, \"rank\": 0.002233021088826114, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 275, \"end\": 281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"score\": 0.7771235322668253, \"rank\": 0.2867959985899609, \"text\": \"Benoit\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\"}, {\"begin\": 290, \"end\": 297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 0.9999999990232027, \"rank\": 9.766758068045586e-10, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 324, \"end\": 330, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5398831083947768, \"rank\": 0.6305752697115813, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 445, \"end\": 450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.450025504870683e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympic rings\", \"from\": 134, \"to\": 151}, {\"ngram\": \"the first floor\", \"from\": 169, \"to\": 184}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 188, \"to\": 204}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympic games\", \"from\": 214, \"to\": 242}, {\"ngram\": \"June\", \"from\": 261, \"to\": 265}, {\"ngram\": \"artificial intelligence\", \"from\": 342, \"to\": 365}, {\"ngram\": \"AI\", \"from\": 367, \"to\": 369}, {\"ngram\": \"the thousands\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 392}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 396, \"to\": 404}, {\"ngram\": \"coaches\", \"from\": 406, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 418, \"to\": 428}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 465}, {\"ngram\": \"a form\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 475}, {\"ngram\": \"surveillance\", \"from\": 488, \"to\": 500}, {\"ngram\": \"rights groups\", \"from\": 502, \"to\": 515}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French authorities have tested artificial intelligence surveillance systems at train stations, concerts, and football matches in recent months.\", \"from\": 525, \"to\": 668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 525, \"end\": 531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5398831083947768, \"rank\": 0.6305752697115813, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"artificial intelligence surveillance systems\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 600}, {\"ngram\": \"train stations\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"concerts\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 628}, {\"ngram\": \"football matches\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"recent months\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the games open in late July, these systems will scan the crowds, check for abandoned packages, detect weapons, and more.\", \"from\": 670, \"to\": 795, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 684}, {\"ngram\": \"late July\", \"from\": 693, \"to\": 702}, {\"ngram\": \"these systems\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 717}, {\"ngram\": \"the crowds\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 738}, {\"ngram\": \"abandoned packages\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 768}, {\"ngram\": \"weapons\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 784}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French officials say these tools will not be fully operational ahead of the games, but from then on police, fire and rescue services, and some French transport security agents will use them until March 31, 2025.\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 1008, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 797, \"end\": 803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5398831083947768, \"rank\": 0.6305752697115813, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 940, \"end\": 946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5398831083947768, \"rank\": 0.6305752697115813, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these tools\", \"from\": 818, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"the games\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"police\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 903}, {\"ngram\": \"fire\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 909}, {\"ngram\": \"rescue services\", \"from\": 914, \"to\": 929}, {\"ngram\": \"March\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 998}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Campaigners worry AI surveillance could become the new normal.\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1072, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Campaigners\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1021}, {\"ngram\": \"AI surveillance\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympics are a huge opportunity to test this type of surveillance under the guise of security issues, and are paving the way to even more intrusive systems such as facial recognition,\\\" Katia Roux, advocacy lead at Amnesty International France, told the Thomson Reuters Foundation.\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1264, \"end\": 1269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Katia\", \"score\": 0.9981135040524517, \"rank\": 0.0018900615408842547, \"text\": \"Katia\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Katia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Battle_of_Katia\"}, {\"begin\": 1293, \"end\": 1314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"score\": 0.9999999999809006, \"rank\": 1.9007024973899523e-11, \"text\": \"Amnesty International\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amnesty_International\"}, {\"begin\": 1315, \"end\": 1321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9977704980706663, \"rank\": 0.002233021088826114, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1332, \"end\": 1358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomson_Reuters_Foundation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomson Reuters Foundation\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomson_Reuters_Foundation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomson_Reuters_Foundation\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1087}, {\"ngram\": \"a huge opportunity\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"this type\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1128}, {\"ngram\": \"surveillance\", \"from\": 1132, \"to\": 1144}, {\"ngram\": \"the guise\", \"from\": 1151, \"to\": 1160}, {\"ngram\": \"security issues\", \"from\": 1164, \"to\": 1179}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 1196, \"to\": 1203}, {\"ngram\": \"even more intrusive systems\", \"from\": 1207, \"to\": 1234}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1261}, {\"ngram\": \"advocacy lead\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1289}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French government has enlisted four companies in the effort - Videtics, Orange Business, ChapsVision and Wintics.\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1365, \"end\": 1371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5398831083947768, \"rank\": 0.6305752697115813, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1437, \"end\": 1443, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\", \"score\": 0.9999999999754436, \"rank\": 2.476957920310105e-11, \"text\": \"Orange\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"four companies\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1410}, {\"ngram\": \"the effort\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1424}, {\"ngram\": \"- Videtics\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1435}, {\"ngram\": \"ChapsVision\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1465}, {\"ngram\": \"Wintics\", \"from\": 1470, \"to\": 1477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The security platforms of these companies measure eight key metrics: traffic that goes against the flow, the presence of people in prohibited zones, crowd movement, abandoned packages, the presence or use of weapons, overcrowding, a body on the ground, and fire.\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1742, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The security platforms\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"these companies\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1521}, {\"ngram\": \"eight key metrics\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1547}, {\"ngram\": \"traffic\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1556}, {\"ngram\": \"the flow\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1583}, {\"ngram\": \"the presence\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1597}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 1601, \"to\": 1607}, {\"ngram\": \"prohibited zones\", \"from\": 1611, \"to\": 1627}, {\"ngram\": \"crowd movement\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"abandoned packages\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"the presence\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1677}, {\"ngram\": \"use\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1684}, {\"ngram\": \"weapons\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1695}, {\"ngram\": \"overcrowding\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1709}, {\"ngram\": \"a body\", \"from\": 1711, \"to\": 1717}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 1721, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"fire\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1741}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Depeche Mode and Black-Eyed Peas concerts, as well as a soccer match between Paris Saint-Germain and Olympique Lyon, have been test sites for the software.\", \"from\": 1744, \"to\": 1899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1744, \"end\": 1756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Depeche_Mode\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Depeche Mode\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Depeche_Mode\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Depeche_Mode\"}, {\"begin\": 1761, \"end\": 1776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_Eyed_Peas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Black-Eyed Peas\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_Eyed_Peas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_Eyed_Peas\"}, {\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.450025504870683e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_Lyonnais\", \"score\": 0.9999999991891855, \"rank\": 8.110226525409681e-10, \"text\": \"Olympique Lyon\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_Lyonnais\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympique_Lyonnais\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a soccer match\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1812}, {\"ngram\": \"test sites\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"the software\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 1898}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More tests were run on crowds travelling through the Nanterre Pr\\u00e9fecture and La Defense Grande Arche metro stations to see Taylor Swift, and the 40,000 attendees of the Cannes Film Festival.\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 2091, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1954, \"end\": 1962, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4992327370346116e-13, \"text\": \"Nanterre\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nanterre\"}, {\"begin\": 1963, \"end\": 1973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prefectures_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.757202930627007e-33, \"text\": \"Pr\\u00e9fecture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prefectures_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prefectures_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1978, \"end\": 1988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\", \"score\": 0.9999999962869879, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"La Defense\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/La_D\\u00e9fense\"}, {\"begin\": 1989, \"end\": 2001, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grande_Arche\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Grande Arche\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grande_Arche\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grande_Arche\"}, {\"begin\": 2024, \"end\": 2036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Swift\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.691198677417125e-33, \"text\": \"Taylor Swift\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Swift\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Swift\"}, {\"begin\": 2070, \"end\": 2076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannes\", \"score\": 0.9999979556871927, \"rank\": 1.964108177234402e-06, \"text\": \"Cannes\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannes\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"More tests\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"crowds\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 1930}, {\"ngram\": \"the 40,000 attendees\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cannes Mayor David Lisnard said the town already had the \\\"densest video protection network in France\\\", with 884 cameras - one for every 84 residents.\", \"from\": 2093, \"to\": 2242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2093, \"end\": 2099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannes\", \"score\": 0.9999979556871927, \"rank\": 1.964108177234402e-06, \"text\": \"Cannes\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cannes\"}, {\"begin\": 2187, \"end\": 2193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9977704980706663, \"rank\": 0.002233021088826114, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the town\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2133}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"densest video protection network\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2183}, {\"ngram\": \"884 cameras\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2212}, {\"ngram\": \"every 84 residents\", \"from\": 2223, \"to\": 2241}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Across France there are about 90,000 video surveillance cameras, monitored by the police and the gendarmerie, according to a 2020 report.\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2381, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"France\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2257}, {\"ngram\": \"about 90,000 video surveillance cameras\", \"from\": 2268, \"to\": 2307}, {\"ngram\": \"the police\", \"from\": 2322, \"to\": 2332}, {\"ngram\": \"the gendarmerie\", \"from\": 2337, \"to\": 2352}, {\"ngram\": \"a 2020 report\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2380}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"One overarching concern is that while the majority of these use cases may not seem to involve revealing the identity of, or profiling, individual people, they still require the deployment of a surveillance infrastructure that is always one software update away from being able to do the most invasive kinds of mass surveillance,\\\" said Daniel Leufer, a senior policy analyst at digital rights group AccessNow.\", \"from\": 2383, \"to\": 2792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2761, \"end\": 2768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_media\", \"score\": 0.9969921045331506, \"rank\": 0.0030169642787646537, \"text\": \"digital\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_media\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One overarching concern\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2407}, {\"ngram\": \"the majority\", \"from\": 2422, \"to\": 2434}, {\"ngram\": \"these use cases\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2453}, {\"ngram\": \"the identity\", \"from\": 2488, \"to\": 2500}, {\"ngram\": \"the deployment\", \"from\": 2557, \"to\": 2571}, {\"ngram\": \"a surveillance infrastructure\", \"from\": 2575, \"to\": 2604}, {\"ngram\": \"one software update\", \"from\": 2620, \"to\": 2639}, {\"ngram\": \"the most invasive kinds\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 2690}, {\"ngram\": \"mass surveillance\", \"from\": 2694, \"to\": 2711}, {\"ngram\": \"Daniel Leufer\", \"from\": 2719, \"to\": 2732}, {\"ngram\": \"a senior policy analyst\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2757}, {\"ngram\": \"AccessNow\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2791}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Members of the public will have little to no oversight about what types of things these systems are monitoring, what updates are made etc, and so we will get the inevitable chilling effect that comes from this type of public surveillance,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 3043, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Members\", \"from\": 2795, \"to\": 2802}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2816}, {\"ngram\": \"no oversight\", \"from\": 2837, \"to\": 2849}, {\"ngram\": \"what types\", \"from\": 2856, \"to\": 2866}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2876}, {\"ngram\": \"these systems\", \"from\": 2877, \"to\": 2890}, {\"ngram\": \"the inevitable chilling effect\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 2983}, {\"ngram\": \"this type\", \"from\": 3000, \"to\": 3009}, {\"ngram\": \"public surveillance\", \"from\": 3013, \"to\": 3032}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French lawmakers have attempted to assuage criticism with a ban on facial recognition.\", \"from\": 3045, \"to\": 3131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3045, \"end\": 3051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5398831083947768, \"rank\": 0.6305752697115813, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"criticism\", \"from\": 3088, \"to\": 3097}, {\"ngram\": \"a ban\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3108}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3130}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Authorities say it is a red line not to be crossed.\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3183, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Authorities\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3143}, {\"ngram\": \"a red line\", \"from\": 3154, \"to\": 3164}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Matthias Houllier, the co-founder of Wintics, said the experiment was \\\"strictly limited\\\" to the eight use-cases outlined in the law, and that features like crowd movement detection could not be used for other processes like gait detection, whereby a person's unique walk can identify them.\", \"from\": 3185, \"to\": 3474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3185, \"end\": 3193, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthias_Corvinus\", \"score\": 0.9849102074855098, \"rank\": 0.006861626542272917, \"text\": \"Matthias\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthias_Corvinus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthias_Corvinus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the co\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3210}, {\"ngram\": \"founder\", \"from\": 3211, \"to\": 3218}, {\"ngram\": \"Wintics\", \"from\": 3222, \"to\": 3229}, {\"ngram\": \"the experiment\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3250}, {\"ngram\": \"the eight use-cases\", \"from\": 3277, \"to\": 3296}, {\"ngram\": \"the law\", \"from\": 3309, \"to\": 3316}, {\"ngram\": \"crowd movement detection\", \"from\": 3341, \"to\": 3365}, {\"ngram\": \"other processes\", \"from\": 3388, \"to\": 3403}, {\"ngram\": \"gait detection\", \"from\": 3409, \"to\": 3423}, {\"ngram\": \"a person's unique walk\", \"from\": 3433, \"to\": 3455}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Houllier said it was \\\"absolutely impossible\\\" both for end-users and advanced engineers to use Wintics for facial recognition due to its design.\", \"from\": 3476, \"to\": 3619, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Houllier\", \"from\": 3476, \"to\": 3484}, {\"ngram\": \"end-users\", \"from\": 3530, \"to\": 3539}, {\"ngram\": \"advanced engineers\", \"from\": 3544, \"to\": 3562}, {\"ngram\": \"Wintics\", \"from\": 3570, \"to\": 3577}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition\", \"from\": 3582, \"to\": 3600}, {\"ngram\": \"its design\", \"from\": 3608, \"to\": 3618}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Representatives from Videtics, Orange Business and ChapsVision did not respond to requests for comment.\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3724, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3652, \"end\": 3658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\", \"score\": 0.9999999999754436, \"rank\": 2.476957920310105e-11, \"text\": \"Orange\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orange_S.A.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Representatives\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3636}, {\"ngram\": \"Videtics\", \"from\": 3642, \"to\": 3650}, {\"ngram\": \"ChapsVision\", \"from\": 3672, \"to\": 3683}, {\"ngram\": \"requests\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3711}, {\"ngram\": \"comment\", \"from\": 3716, \"to\": 3723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Experts have concerns that the way the government is measuring the success of these tests, and the precise way this technology works, has not been made available to the public.\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3902, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Experts\", \"from\": 3726, \"to\": 3733}, {\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 3739, \"to\": 3747}, {\"ngram\": \"the way\", \"from\": 3753, \"to\": 3760}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 3761, \"to\": 3775}, {\"ngram\": \"the success\", \"from\": 3789, \"to\": 3800}, {\"ngram\": \"these tests\", \"from\": 3804, \"to\": 3815}, {\"ngram\": \"the precise way\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3836}, {\"ngram\": \"this technology\", \"from\": 3837, \"to\": 3852}, {\"ngram\": \"the public\", \"from\": 3891, \"to\": 3901}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is nowhere near the necessary amount of transparency about these technologies.\", \"from\": 3904, \"to\": 3989, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the necessary amount\", \"from\": 3927, \"to\": 3947}, {\"ngram\": \"transparency\", \"from\": 3951, \"to\": 3963}, {\"ngram\": \"these technologies\", \"from\": 3970, \"to\": 3988}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a very unfortunate narrative that we cannot permit transparency about such systems, particularly in a law enforcement or public security context, but this is nonsense\\\", Leufer said.\", \"from\": 3990, \"to\": 4180, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a very unfortunate narrative\", \"from\": 3999, \"to\": 4027}, {\"ngram\": \"transparency\", \"from\": 4050, \"to\": 4062}, {\"ngram\": \"such systems\", \"from\": 4069, \"to\": 4081}, {\"ngram\": \"a law enforcement\", \"from\": 4099, \"to\": 4116}, {\"ngram\": \"public security context\", \"from\": 4120, \"to\": 4143}, {\"ngram\": \"nonsense\", \"from\": 4157, \"to\": 4165}, {\"ngram\": \"Leufer\", \"from\": 4168, \"to\": 4174}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The use of surveillance technologies like these, especially in law enforcement and public security contexts, holds perhaps the greatest potential for harm, and therefore requires the highest level of public accountability,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 4182, \"to\": 4415, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The use\", \"from\": 4183, \"to\": 4190}, {\"ngram\": \"surveillance technologies\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4219}, {\"ngram\": \"law enforcement\", \"from\": 4246, \"to\": 4261}, {\"ngram\": \"public security contexts\", \"from\": 4266, \"to\": 4290}, {\"ngram\": \"perhaps the greatest potential\", \"from\": 4298, \"to\": 4328}, {\"ngram\": \"harm\", \"from\": 4333, \"to\": 4337}, {\"ngram\": \"the highest level\", \"from\": 4362, \"to\": 4379}, {\"ngram\": \"public accountability\", \"from\": 4383, \"to\": 4404}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Privacy campaigners say that carve outs in legislation would allow deployment of facial recognition by \\\"competent authorities\\\", for purposes including national security and migration.\", \"from\": 4417, \"to\": 4600, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Privacy campaigners\", \"from\": 4417, \"to\": 4436}, {\"ngram\": \"carve outs\", \"from\": 4446, \"to\": 4456}, {\"ngram\": \"legislation\", \"from\": 4460, \"to\": 4471}, {\"ngram\": \"deployment\", \"from\": 4484, \"to\": 4494}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition\", \"from\": 4498, \"to\": 4516}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"competent authorities\", \"from\": 4520, \"to\": 4542}, {\"ngram\": \"purposes\", \"from\": 4549, \"to\": 4557}, {\"ngram\": \"national security\", \"from\": 4568, \"to\": 4585}, {\"ngram\": \"migration\", \"from\": 4590, \"to\": 4599}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is not a ban.\", \"from\": 4602, \"to\": 4621, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a ban\", \"from\": 4615, \"to\": 4620}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's actually an authorisation for law enforcement agencies.\", \"from\": 4622, \"to\": 4684, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an authorisation\", \"from\": 4638, \"to\": 4654}, {\"ngram\": \"law enforcement agencies\", \"from\": 4659, \"to\": 4683}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People have this illusion that because it says we are banning the technology - except in this, this and this situation - it's okay, but these situations are the most problematic ones,\\\" Roux said.\", \"from\": 4685, \"to\": 4880, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"People\", \"from\": 4685, \"to\": 4691}, {\"ngram\": \"this illusion\", \"from\": 4697, \"to\": 4710}, {\"ngram\": \"the technology\", \"from\": 4747, \"to\": 4761}, {\"ngram\": \"these situations\", \"from\": 4821, \"to\": 4837}, {\"ngram\": \"the most problematic ones\", \"from\": 4842, \"to\": 4867}, {\"ngram\": \"Roux\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 4874}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's historical use of surveillance has also raised concerns.\", \"from\": 4882, \"to\": 4947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4882, \"end\": 4888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9977704980706663, \"rank\": 0.002233021088826114, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"surveillance\", \"from\": 4909, \"to\": 4921}, {\"ngram\": \"concerns\", \"from\": 4938, \"to\": 4946}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In November last year, non-profit Disclose found that law enforcement agencies had covertly used facial recognition software from Israeli company Briefcam since 2015.\", \"from\": 4948, \"to\": 5114, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5078, \"end\": 5085, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 0.6716330674019237, \"rank\": 0.4102968204302284, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"November\", \"from\": 4951, \"to\": 4959}, {\"ngram\": \"non-profit Disclose\", \"from\": 4971, \"to\": 4990}, {\"ngram\": \"law enforcement agencies\", \"from\": 5002, \"to\": 5026}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition software\", \"from\": 5045, \"to\": 5072}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French politicians suggested there was still a gap between the promises made by AI-surveillance, and its capabilities.\", \"from\": 5116, \"to\": 5234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5116, \"end\": 5122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.5398831083947768, \"rank\": 0.6305752697115813, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a gap\", \"from\": 5161, \"to\": 5166}, {\"ngram\": \"the promises\", \"from\": 5175, \"to\": 5187}, {\"ngram\": \"AI-surveillance\", \"from\": 5196, \"to\": 5211}, {\"ngram\": \"its capabilities\", \"from\": 5217, \"to\": 5233}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"AI-driven video surveillance will not be optimal at the time of the Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 5236, \"to\": 5319, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"AI-driven video surveillance\", \"from\": 5237, \"to\": 5265}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 5289, \"to\": 5297}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 5301, \"to\": 5318}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Olympics will be a great playground to experiment with it,\\\" said Senator Agnes Canayer.\", \"from\": 5320, \"to\": 5415, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5324, \"to\": 5336}, {\"ngram\": \"a great playground\", \"from\": 5345, \"to\": 5363}, {\"ngram\": \"Senator Agnes Canayer\", \"from\": 5393, \"to\": 5414}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"More internal security forces or private security forces will be needed to compensate for tech's shortcomings,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 5417, \"to\": 5539, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"More internal security forces\", \"from\": 5418, \"to\": 5447}, {\"ngram\": \"private security forces\", \"from\": 5451, \"to\": 5474}, {\"ngram\": \"tech's shortcomings\", \"from\": 5508, \"to\": 5527}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Ministry of the Interior, which oversees French law enforcement, did not respond to a request for comment.\", \"from\": 5541, \"to\": 5651, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Ministry\", \"from\": 5541, \"to\": 5553}, {\"ngram\": \"the Interior\", \"from\": 5557, \"to\": 5569}, {\"ngram\": \"French law enforcement\", \"from\": 5586, \"to\": 5608}, {\"ngram\": \"a request\", \"from\": 5629, \"to\": 5638}, {\"ngram\": \"comment\", \"from\": 5643, \"to\": 5650}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a list of proposals on the future of AI-enabled surveillance, the government's Law Commission recommended that the \\\"experimental basis\\\" of the technology continue and the retention period of images captured by the systems should also be extended, to \\\"test the equipment over all seasons\\\" and during smaller events.\", \"from\": 5653, \"to\": 5970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5735, \"end\": 5749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_commission\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 2.8935859126260894e-12, \"text\": \"Law Commission\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_commission\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_commission\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a list\", \"from\": 5656, \"to\": 5662}, {\"ngram\": \"proposals\", \"from\": 5666, \"to\": 5675}, {\"ngram\": \"the future\", \"from\": 5679, \"to\": 5689}, {\"ngram\": \"AI-enabled surveillance\", \"from\": 5693, \"to\": 5716}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"experimental basis\", \"from\": 5767, \"to\": 5790}, {\"ngram\": \"the technology\", \"from\": 5795, \"to\": 5809}, {\"ngram\": \"the retention period\", \"from\": 5823, \"to\": 5843}, {\"ngram\": \"images\", \"from\": 5847, \"to\": 5853}, {\"ngram\": \"the systems\", \"from\": 5866, \"to\": 5877}, {\"ngram\": \"the equipment\", \"from\": 5912, \"to\": 5925}, {\"ngram\": \"all seasons\", \"from\": 5931, \"to\": 5942}, {\"ngram\": \"smaller events\", \"from\": 5955, \"to\": 5969}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's why we decided to campaign and raise awareness right now on facial recognition, even if it's not going to be used during the Olympics,\\\" Roux said.\", \"from\": 5972, \"to\": 6126, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"awareness\", \"from\": 6017, \"to\": 6026}, {\"ngram\": \"facial recognition\", \"from\": 6040, \"to\": 6058}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 6101, \"to\": 6113}, {\"ngram\": \"Roux\", \"from\": 6116, \"to\": 6120}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If we wait until it's going to be used, then it's going to be too late.\", \"from\": 6127, \"to\": 6199, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"- Rappler.com How does this make you feel?\", \"from\": 6199, \"to\": 6243, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"follow us\", \"from\": 6245, \"to\": 6254, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 6252, \"to\": 6254}]}]}"